 development with Node.js.What you will learn Build scalable server-side applications using Node.js frameworks Implement asynchronous programming with Promises and Async/Await Design secure authentication using Passport and JWT tokens Develop RESTful and GraphQL APIs for modern web services Create real-time apps leveraging WebSockets and Socket.IO Optimize Node.js performance and deploy scalable microservices Who this book is for Ideal for intermediate developers with basic JavaScript knowledge looking to deepen their server-side skills with Node.js. Familiarity with JavaScript ES6+ is recommended. Readers should have fundamental programming experience and a basic understanding of web technologies. No prior Node.js experience is required.', 837, 'BOOK', 53253, 'KRW', 'Packt Publishing Ltd', '2025-06-19', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=z_5mEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api');
