INSERT IGNORE INTO book (isbn, title, subtitle, description, page_count, format, amount, currency, publisher, published_date, image_url) VALUES ('9791194679714', 'AI Innovations in Disaster Management', NULL, '"**Book Title: AI Innovations in Disaster Management** **Book Description:** In an era marked by increasing climate volatility and the unpredictability of natural disasters, AI Innovations in Disaster Management delves into the transformative role of artificial intelligence in enhancing disaster preparedness, response, and recovery. This comprehensive volume presents a synthesis of cutting-edge research and practical applications that showcase how AI technologies are revolutionizing the field of disaster management. The book explores various AI-driven methodologies such as predictive analytics, machine learning, and real-time data processing that empower emergency services to make informed decisions during crises. Through the lens of risk assessment and resource allocation, readers will gain insights into how AI can optimize response strategies, ensuring that critical resources are deployed efficiently where they are needed most. Throughout the text, the authors emphasize the importance of data visualization and geographic information systems (GIS) in crisis communication, illustrating how these tools can enhance situational awareness among first responders and the communities they serve. The integration of remote sensing and early warning systems is also examined, highlighting advancements that enable timely alerts and proactive measures to mitigate disaster impacts. Moreover, the book addresses the significance of community engagement in disaster resilience planning, demonstrating how AI can facilitate collaboration between authorities and local populations. Simulation models are featured as vital tools for envisioning different disaster scenarios, allowing for better preparedness and strategic planning. With case studies on flood management, wildfire control, and earthquake prediction, AI Innovations in Disaster Management serves as an essential resource for policymakers, emergency management professionals, researchers, and anyone passionate about improving public safety amidst the challenges posed by climate change. This book not only offers a glimpse into the future of disaster management but also provides actionable strategies for fostering resilience in communities worldwide."', 275, 'BOOK', 11000, 'KRW', '타우루스', '2025-02-12', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kxBIEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api');
INSERT IGNORE INTO book (isbn, title, subtitle, description, page_count, format, amount, currency, publisher, published_date, image_url) VALUES ('9791194679431', 'AI-Driven Supply Chain Management', NULL, '"**Book Title: AI-Driven Supply Chain Management** In today''s fast-paced and ever-evolving business landscape, organizations are increasingly turning to artificial intelligence (AI) to revolutionize their supply chain operations. AI-Driven Supply Chain Management serves as a comprehensive guide for professionals seeking to harness the power of AI, machine learning, and predictive analytics to optimize their supply chains. This book delves deep into the multifaceted world of supply chain optimization, exploring how AI technologies can enhance inventory management, demand forecasting, and logistics. Readers will discover innovative strategies for automating processes, leveraging data analytics, and implementing smart warehousing solutions that foster real-time tracking and operational efficiency. The book emphasizes the significance of risk management and supplier relationship dynamics in an agile supply chain, offering practical insights to navigate today''s complex supply chain challenges. Moreover, the text highlights the critical role of sustainability and digital transformation, demonstrating how businesses can reduce costs while improving processes and customer experience. The integration of blockchain and the Internet of Things (IoT) into supply chain management is also explored, illustrating how these technologies can create transparency and resilience within supply chains. With a focus on big data and its implications for decision-making, AI-Driven Supply Chain Management equips readers with the knowledge and tools necessary to thrive in a competitive environment. By adopting AI-driven approaches, organizations can not only achieve operational excellence but also pave the way for future innovations in supply chain management. Whether you are a supply chain professional, a business leader, or a student, this book will inspire you to rethink traditional practices and embrace the transformative potential of AI in your supply chain strategy. Join us on this journey towards a more efficient, intelligent, and sustainable future in supply chain management."', 275, 'BOOK', 11000, 'KRW', '타우루스', '2025-02-12', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WxBIEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api');
INSERT IGNORE INTO book (isbn, title, subtitle, description, page_count, format, amount, currency, publisher, published_date, image_url) VALUES ('9788952130976', 'Smart Land Management and Planning Interventions', NULL, '파괴된 도시에서 스마트 토지관리까지 한국 도시환경의 변화를 읽다 한국은 20세기 중반 전쟁의 후유증과 가난을 극복하고, 신속하고 지속가능한 성장을 이룩했다. 경제가 빠르게 성장하는 가운데 다수의 빈민촌은 오늘날 도시에서 더 이상 찾아보기 어려워졌다. 김세훈 교수를 필두로 한 서울대학교 환경대학원의 도시설계연구실(Urban Studies and Design Lab) 연구진의 긴밀한 협업을 통해 저술된 이 책은 한국전쟁 이후부터 오늘날에 이르기까지 한국의 도시환경을 갖추는 데 기여한 주요 토지관리 정책과 도시개발 사례를 국내외 독자에게 소개한다. 먼저 한국의 지속가능한 성장 모습을 요약하고 고도성장기 도시화에 따른 문제점과 토지갈등을 고찰한다. 그다음 사례로서 1950년대 농지개혁의 의미와 결과, 오늘날 성남시의 원도심을 형성하게 된 광주대단지 조성, 토지구획정리사업 및 서울의 마지막 달동네라 불리는 백사마을 재개발 등을 다루었고, 토지소유 및 사용권의 제도화와 최근 도입된 디지털 정보를 활용한 스마트 토지관리정책 등도 살펴본다. South Korea is well known for its transition from an impoverished nation to a model of rapid, sustainable growth. The economy emerged quickly away from the post-war damage, and the spread of illegal settlements was mitigated. The book describes a set of policies and planning actions implemented in the country''s fragile condition from the aftermath of the war in the 1950s to the present. The desirable state of balanced growth was supported by secured access to land for efficient uses and the governments'' timely intervention in the conflicts between landowners and de facto occupants. Careful management of land registration and land-related information is notable, and the promotion of land development for the benefit of the public has also been carried out. Despite ongoing debate on equitable land distribution, the unevenness of property ownership and imbalanced gain from real estate transactions were addressed based on public policies, with mixed results. Some cases like the Farmland Reform in the 1950s, the making of Gwangju Resettlement Town situated in today''s Seongnam, the processes of Land Readjustment Projects, and the redevelopment of the 104 Village - often referred to as the last moon village in Seoul - were included. The book is an outcome of collaborative research in Urban Studies and Design Lab at Seoul National University Graduate School of Environmental Studies.', 249, 'BOOK', 34000, 'KRW', 'Seoul National University Press', '2021-10-06', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LddKEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api');
INSERT IGNORE INTO book (isbn, title, subtitle, description, page_count, format, amount, currency, publisher, published_date, image_url) VALUES ('9791194679790', 'Smart Energy Solutions: Harnessing AI for Efficient Management', NULL, '"Smart Energy Solutions: Harnessing AI for Efficient Management is an insightful guide that explores the transformative power of artificial intelligence in the energy sector. As we face the urgent challenges of climate change and the increasing demand for sustainable energy, this book provides a comprehensive look at how AI-driven technologies can enhance energy efficiency and management. The narrative begins by establishing the importance of smart grids and renewable energy sources, emphasizing their role in creating a resilient and adaptable energy infrastructure. The authors delve into predictive analytics and machine learning, demonstrating how these tools can optimize energy consumption and reduce carbon footprints. By employing real-time monitoring and smart metering, consumers and energy providers alike can gain actionable insights into energy usage patterns, leading to more informed decision-making. Furthermore, the book addresses the significance of demand response programs and load forecasting in balancing energy supply and demand. It illustrates how data analytics and IoT devices can facilitate automation in power distribution, ensuring efficient energy flow while minimizing wastage. The discussion extends to energy storage solutions, highlighting their crucial role in maximizing renewable energy utilization and stabilizing the grid. Throughout the text, the authors provide case studies and practical examples that showcase successful implementations of AI technologies in energy management. They also examine consumer behavior and energy policy, illustrating how informed policies can drive the transition to sustainable energy practices. Smart Energy Solutions is a must-read for energy professionals, policymakers, and anyone interested in understanding the intersection of technology and sustainability. By harnessing the potential of AI, we can pave the way for a more energy-efficient future, reduce emissions, and combat climate change, ensuring a sustainable world for generations to come."', 259, 'BOOK', 11000, 'KRW', '타우루스', '2025-02-12', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oxBIEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api');
